# Project Context

> **Cursor & Lovable:** Policy in root `AGENTS.md` (Lovable always reads it) + `.cursor/rules/` (Cursor). Keep both in sync when editing rules.

**ChatCRM** — omnichannel inbox + CRM for laundry/salon businesses. Demo app; all data in `src/lib/store.tsx`.

## Stack

TanStack Start + Router, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind 4, shadcn/ui (new-york), Recharts, Bun.

## Where things live

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| Routes | `src/routes/*.tsx` (file-based) |
| Global state | `src/lib/store.tsx` |
| Auth | `useAuth` → `currentAgent` in store |
| Customers + RFM | `useCustomers`, `lib/rfm.ts`, `lib/clv.ts`, `lib/cadence.ts` |
| Chat | `components/chat/ChatPage.tsx`, `useConversations` |
| RBAC | `lib/permissions.ts` — always use helpers, never duplicate role checks |
| Seed data | `src/data/*.ts` |
| Types | `src/types/index.ts` |
| Zod schemas | `src/lib/schemas/` (create when adding forms/API) |

## Lovable constraint

Never force-push or rewrite pushed git history (rebase/amend/squash on shared branch). Keep main branch buildable.

## Demo constants

RFM/CLV/cadence use fixed reference date `DEMO_NOW` in `lib/demo.ts` (2026-06-18). Do not mix with `Date.now()` in the same calculation path without unifying.

## Adding a feature checklist

1. Type in `src/types/index.ts` if new entity/field
2. Seed or store action in `store.tsx`
3. Permission in `permissions.ts` if role-gated
4. Hook if derived/filtered data is reused
5. Route or section in existing page
6. `logAudit` if user-visible security action
7. Zod schema in `src/lib/schemas/` if form or validated input — see `validation-schema.mdc`
